\par ABILITY SCORES
\par }{\fs20\insrsid7804164 Every character has six basic Ability Scores:
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \ql \fi-360\li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx720\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls1\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\insrsid7804164 Strength (STR)
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Dexterity (DEX)
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Constitution (CON)
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Intelligence (INT)
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Wisdom (WIS)
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Charisma (CHA) 
\par }\pard\plain \s17\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\insrsid7804164 
The Score of these Abilities ranges from 0 to infinity.  A limit, if any, will be specified in the rules.  The normal human range is 3 to 18. It is possible for a creature to have a score of "none".  A score of "none" is not the same as a score of "0".  A
 score of "none" means that the creature does not possess the ability at all.  The modifier for a score of "none" is +0.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \ql \fi-360\li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx720\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls2\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\insrsid7804164 STR 0 means that the character cannot move at all. He lies helpless on the ground.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}DEX 0 means that the character cannot move at all. He stands motionless, rigid, and helpless.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}CON 0 means that the character is dead.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}INT 0 means that the character cannot think and is unconscious in a coma like stupor, helpless.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}WIS 0 means that the character is withdrawn into a deep sleep filled with nightmares, helpless.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}CHA 0 means that the character is withdrawn into a catatonic, coma like stupor, helpless.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\insrsid7804164 Keeping track of negative ability score points is never necessary. A character\rquote s ability score can\rquote 
