\par }\pard\plain \s17\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\ul\insrsid7804164 ABILITY MODIFIERS
\par }{\fs20\insrsid7804164 Each ability will have a modifier. The modifier can be calculated using this formula: 
\par (ability/2) -5 [round result down] 
\par The modifier is the number you add to or subtract from the die roll when your character tries to do something related to that ability. A positive modifier is called a bonus, and a negative modifier is called a penalty. 
\par }{\fs20\ul\insrsid7804164 USE OF ABILITY SCORES
\par }{\cs18\i\fs20\insrsid7804164 Strength}{\fs20\insrsid7804164 
\par Any creature that can physically manipulate other objects has at least 1 point of Strength. 
\par A creature with no Strength score can't exert force, usually because it has no physical body or because it doesn't move. The creature automatically fails Strength check
s. If the creature can attack, it applies its Dexterity modifier to its base attack instead of a Strength modifier. 
\par }{\cs18\i\fs20\insrsid7804164 Dexterity}{\fs20\insrsid7804164 
\par Any creature that can move has at least 1 point of Dexterity. 
\par A creature with no Dexterity score can't move. If it can act, it applies its Intelligence modifier to initiative checks instead of a Dexterity modifier. The creature fails all Reflex saves and Dexterity checks. 
\par }{\cs18\i\fs20\insrsid7804164 Constitution}{\fs20\insrsid7804164 
\par If a character's Constitution changes enough to alter his or her Constitution modifier, his or her hit points also increase or decrease accordingly at the same time. 
\par Any living creature has at least 1 point of Constitution. 
\par A creature with no Constitution has no body or no metabolism. It is immune to any effect that requires a Fortitude save unless 
the effect works on objects. The creature is also immune to ability damage, ability drain, and energy drain, and always fails Constitution checks. 
\par }{\cs18\i\fs20\insrsid7804164 Intelligence}{\fs20\insrsid7804164 
\par Any creature that can think, learn, or remember has at least 1 point of Intelligence. 
\par A creatu
re with no Intelligence score is an automaton, operating on simple instincts or programmed instructions. It is immune to all mind-influencing effects (charms, compulsions, phantasms, patterns and morale effects) and automatically fails Intelligence checks
. 
\par }{\cs18\i\fs20\insrsid7804164 Wisdom}{\fs20\insrsid7804164 
\par Any creature that can perceive its environment in any fashion has at least 1 point of Wisdom. 
\par Anything with no Wisdom score is an object, not a creature. Anything without a Wisdom score also has no Charisma score, and vice versa. 
\par }{\cs18\i\fs20\insrsid7804164 Charisma}{\fs20\insrsid7804164 
\par Any creature capable of telling the difference between itself and things that are not itself has at least 1 point of Charisma. 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7804164 \strike\fs24\ul\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\strike0\fs20\cf1\insrsid7804164\charrsid7804164 
